Wait, the array is declared as long long int ara[200000]. So each element is a long long. So when reading, the correct format specifier is %lld. So the missing code in the first for loop is:

scanf("%lld", &ara[i]);

Because that's how you read a long long int in C with scanf. So the original code is missing that part. So the first for loop is supposed to read the elements into the array, then sort them in descending order. So that's the missing line. The rest of the code seems to be handling the rest correctly.
